HEADWORD: neuropsychology
<hw>neuropsychology</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the branch of psychology
that is concerned with the physiological bases of psychological
processes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> physiological psychology,
psychophysiology.</syn>⟦br⟧
